name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Congratulations to @NJOHSP Director Laurie Doran! I look forward to continuing to work together.

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: 25 years ago a Jersey kid, Brevin Knight, dominated March Madness & inspired me to work harder & follow my dreams.   This morning I told my son that @PeacocksMBB proves that anything is possible. Millions of kids will believe the same. That’s what makes this so special. #StrutUp

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Happy National Peacock Day!   These guys from @PeacocksMBB give me hope. Don’t bet against Jersey!   #StrutUp

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Had an awesome time running the ⁦@nyrr⁩ NYC Half Marathon this morning! Perfect weather, amazing views, and great to be with 25k other runners for a fun run!  https://t.co/BNoV8t6AQ2

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Congratulations @saintpetersuniv! Jersey heart on full display. What a game!

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Congratulations to my good friend @ShereefElnahal! His commitment to delivering quality healthcare to underserved communities will benefit veterans across our nation.

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Day one in the books. I could not be more excited to serve the residents of our state.  Thank you to @GovMurphy for the confidence you have placed in me.   As promised, we got right to work. Looking forward to tomorrow.

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Andrew Bruck was a friend long before he became a colleague. He is a true public servant to whom every New Jerseyan owes a debt of gratitude — and I know his impact is only just beginning. I thank him for his exemplary service and wish him and his beautiful family my very best.

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: I am grateful, from the bottom of my heart, to @GovMurphy for the trust he has placed in me. And thank you to my good friend @NewJerseyOAG Andrew Bruck for his exemplary service to the state. I will work tirelessly to protect the 9m residents who call this great state home.

name: Matt Platkin
tweet: Colonel Callahan is just about the finest person I’ve had the privilege of working with and calling a friend. A lifelong public servant and the embodiment of a Trooper, we are lucky to have him lead the women and men of @NJSP. Congratulations to the Superintendent and his family.
